Job_Description:
Basic Purpose:
Through evaluations of the resilience and security of critical infrastructure systems at local, regional, national, and global levels, provides analytical support to the Decision and Infrastructure Sciences (DIS) Division. This role includes examining and developing tools, datasets, and strategies for assessing the security and resilience of critical infrastructure assets and systems. This applied research includes:
Identifying relevant human-caused threats and natural hazards, including (but not limited to) future implications related to climate change;
Analyzing asset and system vulnerabilities to various threats and hazards;
Evaluating consequences of disruption or destruction of infrastructure systems, including estimating potential cascading impacts on related infrastructure and essential services (transportation, water, food, finance, emergency services, telecommunications, etc.);
Research Development (RD)
Infrastructure Assurance Analysis 2
Regular
Full time

